A Change Of Pace - Just No Better Way (2008)

Just No Better Way is the second EP released by pop punk band A Change of Pace. It is the first album to include the vocals of new singer, Micah Bentley. The music on this album is a completely new sound, being a lighter style of pop punk and indie rock compared to the older, heavier post-hardcore style under former singer Torry Jasper who also incorporated 'screaming' vocals. The album contains five new songs, and also acoustic versions of the songs. The EP title is a lyric from the song &quot;I Found Myself Today&quot;.

